## Project structure

```
webcraft-ai/
├── index.html        ← The entire frontend (one file)
├── api/
│   └── generate.js   ← Backend API (keeps your key secret)
├── package.json      ← Node config
├── vercel.json       ← Routing config
└── README.md         ← This file
```

---

## How it works

1. User fills in business name, type, description, contact details, and picks a style
2. Frontend sends the data to `/api/generate` on your server
3. Your server calls Gemini with your secret API key
4. Gemini generates a full professional HTML website
5. User sees a live preview and can download or publish it

The API key never touches the user's browser — it stays safely on the server.

